---
description: Instructions on creating and storing cursor rules
globs: *.mdc
alwaysApply: false
---
# Cursor Rules Location

Rules for placing and organizing Cursor rule files in the repository.

<rule>
name: cursor_rules_location
description: Standards for placing Cursor rule files in the correct directory
filters:
  # Match any .mdc files
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.mdc$"
  # Match files that look like Cursor rules
  - type: content
    pattern: "(?s)<rule>.*?</rule>"
  # Match file creation events
  - type: event
    pattern: "file_create"

actions:
  - type: reject
    conditions:
      - pattern: "^(?!\\.\\/\\.cursor\\/rules\\/.*\\.mdc$)"
        message: "Cursor rule files (.mdc) must be placed in the .cursor/rules directory"

  - type: suggest
    message: |
      When creating Cursor rules:

      1. Rules must be placed in PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/rules/:
         ```
         .cursor/rules/
         ├── your-rule-name.mdc
         ├── another-rule.mdc
         └── ...
         ```

      2. Follow the naming convention:
         - Use kebab-case for filenames
         - Always use .mdc extension
         - Make names descriptive of the rule's purpose

      3. Important Note About Rule Creation:
         The AI assistant cannot directly create or modify files in the .cursor/rules directory.
         Instead, when requesting a new rule, the AI will:
         - Provide the filename that should be created
         - Print the complete contents that should go in that file
         - You (the user) will need to manually create the file with the provided contents

      4. Rule File Template:
         ```markdown
         ---
         Description: Brief description of what this rule does
         Globs: **/*.ext, **/pattern/**
         ---
         # Rule Title

         Detailed description of the rule's purpose and behavior.

         <rule>
         name: rule_name
         description: One-line description for the rule
         filters:
           - type: file_extension
             pattern: "pattern"
           # Add more filters...

         actions:
           - type: suggest
             message: |
               Action description
           # Add more actions...

         examples:
           - input: |
               Example input
             output: "Example output"

         metadata:
           priority: high
           version: 1.0
         </rule>
         ```

      5. Directory structure:
         ```
         PROJECT_ROOT/
         ├── .cursor/
         │   └── rules/
         │       ├── your-rule-name.mdc
         │       └── ...
         └── ...
         ```

      6. Never place rule files:
         - In the project root
         - In subdirectories outside .cursor/rules
         - In any other location

examples:
  - input: |
      User: "Create a rule for TypeScript naming conventions"
    output: |
      Please create the following file:

      Filename: .cursor/rules/typescript-naming.mdc

      Contents:
      ```markdown
      ---
      description: TypeScript naming conventions
      globs: "**/*.ts"
      ---
      # TypeScript Naming Conventions

      <rule>
      name: typescript_naming
      description: Standards for naming in TypeScript files
      ...
      </rule>
      ```

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
</rule>